    <p>“I cannot pretend to be sorry,” said Wickham, after a short interruption, “that he or that any man should not be estimated beyond their <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="deserts"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(应得的奖励或惩罚)</code></b>, but with him I believe it does not often happen.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>But when the <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="living"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(牧师职位)</code></b> <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="fell"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(突然来到/突然出现)</code></b>, it was given elsewhere.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="Allowing for |  to think about or plan for (something that will or might happen in the future)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(应付着)</code></b> the common demands of the game, Mr. Wickman was therefore <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="at leisure"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(从容地/不慌不忙地)</code></b> to talk to Elizabeth, and she was very willing to hear him.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>But I have no reason for avoiding him, but what I might proclaim to all the world, <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="a sense of"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(有一种...的感觉)</code></b> <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="very great ill usage"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(遭受极其不公待遇)</code></b>, and most painful regrets at his being what he is.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>And I can never be <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="in company with"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(与...为伍/与...待在一起)</code></b> this Mr. Darcy without being <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="grieved to the soul by a thousand tender recollections"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(因为想起种种昔日往事痛彻心扉)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
